<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="223" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1090,1802]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1090,1115]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[702,865,1090,1114]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Leucophenga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuspidata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[702,717,1091,1114]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[734,865,1090,1114]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">bicuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[874,966,1090,1115]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[874,966,1090,1115]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having the mesonotum and scutellum entirely yellowish in male (
<figureCitation box="[463,540,1126,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[335,1247,195,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[335,1248,195,1937]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal and lateral view of thorax: A, B. Leucophenga argentata in male; C, D. L. argentata in female; E, F. L. bicuspidata sp. nov. in male; G, H. L. bicuspidata sp. nov. in female; I, J. L. fuscivena sp. nov. in male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
E, 
<date box="[574,600,1127,1151]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">4I</date>
), and in the color patterns of abdominal tergites in male (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1323,1126,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,211,1752]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1773]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Abdominal tergites patterns: A – D. Leucophenga argentata; E, F. L. bicuspidata sp. nov.; G – I. L. fuscivena sp. nov.; J – L. L. longipenis sp. nov.; M. L. quadricuspidata sp. nov.; N. L. tricuspidata sp. nov.; O. Color legend." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
E, N), but can be distinguished from the latter by having the aedeagus dorsolaterally with a thin process and distolaterally with three acute processes (
<figureCitation box="[459,539,1198,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[156,1427,770,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,759,1811]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Leucophenga tricuspidata sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods and aedeagus; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus, acute processes (ap) and thin process (tp). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264559/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="223" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1090,1802]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1234,1259]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Description.</emphasis>
Ocellar triangle brownish, with ca. 2 setae above ocellar setae. Frons yellow. Pedicel yellowish; first flagellomere yellow. Clypeus brownish yellow. Palpus brownish yellow. Postpronotal lobe yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1411,1270,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[337,1250,193,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[337,1251,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal and lateral view of thorax: A, B. Leucophenga fuscivena sp. nov. in female; C, D. L. longipenis sp. nov. in male; E, F. L. longipenis sp. nov. in female; G, H. L. quadricuspidata sp. nov. in male; I, J. L. tricuspidata sp. nov. in male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264552/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
J). Acrostichal setulae in ca. 8 irregular rows (
<figureCitation box="[651,722,1306,1331]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[337,1250,193,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[337,1251,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal and lateral view of thorax: A, B. Leucophenga fuscivena sp. nov. in female; C, D. L. longipenis sp. nov. in male; E, F. L. longipenis sp. nov. in female; G, H. L. quadricuspidata sp. nov. in male; I, J. L. tricuspidata sp. nov. in male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264552/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">
Fig. 
<date box="[706,722,1306,1330]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">4</date>
</figureCitation>
I). Pleura, katepisternum and meron yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[1269,1340,1306,1331]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[337,1250,193,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[337,1251,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal and lateral view of thorax: A, B. Leucophenga fuscivena sp. nov. in female; C, D. L. longipenis sp. nov. in male; E, F. L. longipenis sp. nov. in female; G, H. L. quadricuspidata sp. nov. in male; I, J. L. tricuspidata sp. nov. in male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264552/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
J). Wing (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1342,1367]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,679,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,679,1664]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Wing of male: A. Leucophenga argentata; B. L. bicuspidata sp. nov.; C. L. fuscivena sp. nov.; D. L. longipenis sp. nov.; E. L. quadricuspidata sp. nov.; F. L. tricuspidata sp. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264550/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
F): Costal vein between R2+3 and R4+5 distally with ca. 5 peg-like spinules on ventral surface. Only 4th to 6th abdominal tergites with black patches in male (
<figureCitation box="[685,752,1381,1406]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,211,1752]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1773]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Abdominal tergites patterns: A – D. Leucophenga argentata; E, F. L. bicuspidata sp. nov.; G – I. L. fuscivena sp. nov.; J – L. L. longipenis sp. nov.; M. L. quadricuspidata sp. nov.; N. L. tricuspidata sp. nov.; O. Color legend." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
N). Male terminalia: Epandrium with a few pubescence near posterior and ventral margin, with ca. 4 setae near posterior margin and ventral corner per side (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1400,1417,1442]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[156,1427,770,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,759,1811]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Leucophenga tricuspidata sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods and aedeagus; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus, acute processes (ap) and thin process (tp). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264559/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
A). Paramere nearly triangular, narrowed basally and apically, with ca. 3 sensilla distally (
<figureCitation box="[1115,1195,1453,1478]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[156,1427,770,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,759,1811]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Leucophenga tricuspidata sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods and aedeagus; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus, acute processes (ap) and thin process (tp). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264559/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
