<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="223" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1090,1802]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1741,1766]" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">Etymology.</emphasis>
A combination of the Latin words “ 
<emphasis box="[775,811,1742,1765]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">tri-</emphasis>
” (= three) + “ 
<emphasis box="[989,1109,1741,1765]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="223">cuspidatus</emphasis>
” (= acute), referring to the aedeagus distolaterally with three acute processes.
</paragraph>
